==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Willow-herb
<hw>Wil"low-herb`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A perennial herb (<spn>Epilobium spicatum</spn>) with narrow
willowlike leaves and showy rose-purple flowers. The name is sometimes
made to include other species of the same genus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Spiked willow-herb</b></col>, <cd>a perennial herb
(<spn>Lythrum Salicaria</spn>) with willowy leaves and spiked purplish
flowers.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Willowish</ent>⟦br⟧
